The likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are: cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY. 

The paper discusses a solution for SemEval 2019 Task 8 on Fact-Checking in Community Forums, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. 

The paper also mentions the use of neural networks and embeddings, which are common in sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

Furthermore, the task involves classification and decision-making, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). 

Overall, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL, followed by cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, and cs.CY.
